{{#> base subject="SLA BREACH — {{txnId}} — {{phase}} — {{daysOverdue}} days overdue"}}
  {{#*inline "body"}}
    <div class="danger-banner">
      🚨 <strong>SLA BREACH — Immediate Action Required</strong>
    </div>

    <h2>SLA Breach Alert</h2>
    <p>A transaction has exceeded its SLA target for the current phase. This requires immediate attention to avoid further delays and client impact.</p>

    <div class="stat-box">
      <div class="label">Transaction Reference</div>
      <div class="value" style="font-size:14px;font-family:monospace;">{{txnId}}</div>
      <div class="label" style="margin-top:12px;">Breached Phase</div>
      <div class="value">{{upper phase}}</div>
      <div class="label" style="margin-top:12px;">Phase Entered</div>
      <div class="value" style="font-size:14px;">{{enteredAt}}</div>
      <div class="label" style="margin-top:12px;">Days Overdue</div>
      <div class="value" style="color:#DC2626;">{{daysOverdue}} days</div>
    </div>

    <p><strong>Required actions:</strong></p>
    <ol>
      <li>Review the transaction immediately in the AOP Operations Portal.</li>
      <li>Identify the root cause of the delay.</li>
      <li>Contact the responsible party (agent, refinery, or client) to expedite.</li>
      <li>Document the reason for the delay in the transaction notes.</li>
    </ol>

    <hr class="divider" />
    <p style="color:#888;font-size:13px;">SLA breaches are automatically flagged in the compliance audit trail. Repeated breaches may affect agent performance scores.</p>
  {{/inline}}
{{/base}}
